FPUS53 KPAH 171529
ZFPPAH

Zone Forecast Product
National Weather Service Paducah KY
1028 AM CDT Sun Aug 17 2025

KYZ005-172100-
McCracken-
Including the city of Paducah
1028 AM CDT Sun Aug 17 2025

...HEAT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM CDT /8 PM EDT/
TUESDAY...

.TODAY...Sunny. A slight chance of showers and thunderstorms this
afternoon. Hot with highs in the upper 90s. North winds around
5 mph. Chance of rain 20 percent.
.TONIGHT...Partly cloudy with a slight chance of showers and
thunderstorms in the evening, then mostly clear after midnight.
Lows in the mid 70s. Northeast winds around 5 mph in the evening,
becoming light and variable. Chance of rain 20 percent.
.MONDAY...Sunny, hot with highs in the upper 90s. Calm winds,
becoming northeast around 5 mph in the afternoon. Highest heat
index readings heat index readings up to 107 in the afternoon.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Lows in the mid 70s. Calm winds.
.TUESDAY...Sunny, hot with highs in the upper 90s. Calm winds,
becoming northwest around 5 mph in the afternoon. Highest heat
index readings heat index readings up to 105 in the afternoon.
.TUESDAY NIGHT AND WEDNESDAY...Partly cloudy. A chance of showers
and thunderstorms. Lows in the lower 70s. Highs in the lower 90s.
Chance of rain 40 percent.
.WEDNESDAY NIGHT THROUGH THURSDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy. Lows
around 70. Highs in the upper 80s.
.FRIDAY THROUGH SATURDAY...Mostly clear. Highs in the lower 90s.
Lows in the upper 60s.

$$

INZ086-172100-
Vanderburgh-
Including the city of Evansville
1028 AM CDT Sun Aug 17 2025

...HEAT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM CDT /8 PM EDT/
TUESDAY...

.TODAY...Mostly sunny. A slight chance of showers and
thunderstorms this afternoon. Hot with highs in the mid 90s.
North winds around 5 mph. Chance of rain 20 percent.
.TONIGHT...Partly cloudy with a slight chance of showers and
thunderstorms in the evening, then mostly clear after midnight.
Lows in the mid 70s. Northeast winds around 5 mph. Chance of rain
20 percent.
.MONDAY...Sunny, hot with highs in the mid 90s. Northeast winds
around 5 mph. Highest heat index readings heat index readings up
to 105 in the afternoon.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Lows in the mid 70s. Northeast
winds around 5 mph in the evening, becoming light and variable.
.TUESDAY...Sunny, hot with highs in the upper 90s. Southeast
winds around 5 mph, becoming northwest around 5 mph in the
afternoon.
.TUESDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy. A chance of showers and
thunderstorms in the evening. Lows in the lower 70s. Chance of
rain 30 percent.
.WEDNESDAY...Partly sunny with a chance of showers and
thunderstorms. Highs in the upper 80s. Chance of rain 30 percent.
.WEDNESDAY NIGHT AND THURSDAY...Partly cloudy. Lows in the upper
60s. Highs in the upper 80s.
.THURSDAY NIGHT THROUGH SATURDAY...Mostly clear. Lows in the
upper 60s. Highs around 90.

$$

